info: This was the bands network television debut.

At the start of the encore, Dave allowed a local band called 'Humbuck Squash' to play a couple of songs, after listening to their demo tape prior to the show. This was reportedly their first live performance.
This was a benefit show for The Joint Artists & Music Promotions Action Committee (JAMPAC), which was setup by former Nirvana bassist Krist Novoselic.
This was an acoustic performance with only Dave and Pat.

Foo Fighters first performance in the UK and Europe. Before "Winnebago", Dave discounted the media rumours and told the crowd that none of his songs were about his late former bandmate, Kurt Cobain. "Floaty" was on the setlist, but was not played.
Dave talks about how the band had played at the Earth Jam earlier in the day (as part of Mike Watt's backing band), and that Mike Watt had lost his shoes.

Benefit show fundraising for the investigation into the murder of' The Gits' singer Mia Zapata; 'The Presidents of the United States of America' also performed. "X-Static" was on the written setlist, but was not played; "Butterflies" was performed in its place.
Foo Fighters' first public show; opening for The Unseen; setlist incomplete; Dave also played drums with The Unseen on The Beatles' "Slow Down" during their headline set.
First live performance; a private show for family and friends.
